    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 180\u00b0C/ 160\u00b0C (fan)/ 350\u00b0F/ Gas 4</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/valentines-pan-fried-scallops-brown-butter-sauce-and-mash/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p><p>Re-boil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/valentines-pan-fried-scallops-brown-butter-sauce-and-mash/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, add the <strong>hazelnuts</strong>\u00a0to a baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 3-5 min or until toasted</p><p>Once toasted, set aside to cool slightly</p><p>Chop the <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks, then cut the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into wedges</p><p>Chop the <strong>cooled hazelnuts</strong> roughly</p><p>Pat the\u00a0<strong>king scallops</strong>\u00a0dry with <strong>kitchen paper</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/valentines-pan-fried-scallops-brown-butter-sauce-and-mash/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once very hot, add the\u00a0<strong>scallops</strong>\u00a0and cook for 2 min on one side, or until golden brown</p><p>Flip the\u00a0<strong>scallops</strong>\u00a0and cook for 1 min further or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your scallops are cooked when they turn opaque</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/valentines-pan-fried-scallops-brown-butter-sauce-and-mash/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the<strong> potatoes</strong> to a low heat and mash until smooth</p><p>Stir through the <strong>clotted cream</strong> and season generously with <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/valentines-pan-fried-scallops-brown-butter-sauce-and-mash/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim the woody ends off the <strong>asparagus spears</strong></p><p>Tip: Alternatively, bend the woody ends of the asparagus until they snap!</p><p>Add the <strong>trimmed</strong> <strong>asparagus</strong> <strong>spears</strong> to a separate pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> (just enough to cover them) with a pinch of salt, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender</p><p>Once done, drain and return to the pan</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/valentines-pan-fried-scallops-brown-butter-sauce-and-mash/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the scallops are done, transfer them to a plate and return the pan to a medium heat with 40g <span class=\"text-danger\">[80g]</span> <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until the butter starts to brown</p><p>Once brown, stir through the <strong>chopped parsley</strong>, <strong>juice</strong> of 1 <span class=\"text-danger\">[2]</span><strong> lemon wedge<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and <strong>capers</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>brown butter sauce</strong></p><p>Return the <strong>scallops</strong> to the sauce and cook for 30 secs until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/valentines-pan-fried-scallops-brown-butter-sauce-and-mash/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>scallops</strong> over the <strong>mash</strong>\u00a0with the <strong>asparagus</strong> <strong>spears</strong> to the side</p><p>Spoon over the <strong>brown butter sauce</strong> and garnish with the <strong>chopped hazelnuts </strong>and a <strong>lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
